products.title: 50% off Seconds quality yarns
products.body_html:
The yarns in this section are 2nds quality and are being sold at a 50% discount. If you have a use for imperfect skeins, this is a wonderful deal!

These yarns are FINAL SALE and have any of the following problems:
Uneven dyeing
Dirty spots
Tangled skeins
Overspun yarn
Underspun yarn
Felted spots
Last few skeins of a dye lot
Short skeins 

I cannot send photos of the specific skeins, but can try to answer basic questions if you email info@o-wool.com. For the most part, you'll have to take what you get. That's all part of the fun, right?

products.body_html:
Worsted Weight

Fiber Content:
50% alpaca from local farms in NJ & PA
50% certified organic merino
Put-up: 3.5 oz / 100g
Yardage: 240 yds / 219m
Gauge: 18 - 20 sts = 4” / 10cm
Needle: 7 - 9 US / 4.5 - 5.5mm

How about Local dyed with Natural Dyes!?

Click here for patterns in Local

Want to see all of the colors in person before ordering? Order a Shade Card.

Want your yarn wound into balls? Look here.

After one adventurous drive in a minivan brimming with alpaca fiber, O-Wool Local was born. Since then, I've visited farms all around the Philadelphia area collecting fiber. Local is processed in the Northeastern USA. It is squishy and soft, and still has that alpaca smell and some lanolin left in the fiber. It is a truly rustic, minimally processed yarn - if that's your thing, you're going to love this yarn.

Hand wash in cold water with gentle detergent. Lay flat to dry.

PRICE IS PER OUNCE

100% certified organic merino wool 21.5 micron tops in a natural, undyed color.

1 oz / 28g is approx 42" / 1 m.

Tops are similar to roving but are combed instead of carded. All of the short fibers have been removed and what is left are long, unbelievably soft merino wool fibers that are all aligned. This stuff is so silky and soft it's kind of unbelievable...

These tops are ready for your tapestry weaving, hand spinning or felting adventures.

products.title: Cones
products.body_html:
- Balance cones are approx. 2.75 lbs and approx. 3200 yards.
- Chunky Merino cone is approx. 3.1 lbs and approx. 2342 yards.
- Classic Worsted cone is approx. 3.6 lbs. and approx. 3250 yards.
- Legacy Bulky cone is approx. 2.5 lbs and approx. 1220 yards.
- Local cone is approx. 2.6 lbs and approx. 2845 yards.

Want to knit a sweater? A large blanket? Are you a machine knitter or weaver? Hand dyer? These cones are perfect for you!

Cones are only available undyed. These yarns are straight from the mill and have not been scoured/washed/finished in any way. Scour before dyeing. Work up a swatch and wash it accordingly before deciding on your gauge - the yarn blooms substantially upon washing. Alternately, you can skein it up, tie up the skeins securely, wash them first and work from "finished" yarn.

Cones are final sale - I cannot offer exchanges or returns on cones. If you want to try it before you buy it, buy a skein!

Fog Cutter is versatile, flattering, and easy to throw on. It features a beautiful combination of cables, lace, and texture in a panel that undulates like waves over small stones. A split hem, some ribbed detail, and boldly seamed shoulders also add to the interest on this design, and reverse stockinette on sleeves and back keep the focus on the details.
